-- Afghan Army Cuts May Aid Taliban, Frankfurter Allgemeine Reports
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 2012-02-11T16:32:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-11/afghan-army-cuts-may-aid-taliban-frankfurter-allgemeine-reports.html
German Defense Minister Thomas de Maiziere said reducing the number of Afghan security forces to
230,000 from 350,000 may lead to an increase in Taliban
fighters, Frankfurter Allgemeine Sonntagszeitung reported
in an e-mailed summary of an article to be published tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicholas Comfort in Frankfurt at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
